InSim.NET is a library for windows based InSim applications developed inside Visual Studio. The application is made for the online car simulator, Live For Speed.
The InSim tracks your speed, kmh, mph, xy postion, boxes, text messages etc. About everything.

FeedPackage.Description: .NET InSim library for the online racing simulator Live for Speed
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Various improvements to InSim.Send() methods. Fixed bug where OutSim.IsConnected would throw a exception if no connection timeout was specified. Unicode string encoding is now more strict.

FeedPackage.Description: .NET InSim library for the online racing simulator Live for Speed
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * InSim.NET now requires .NET 4.5 or better * Added missing leave reasons * Fixed string encoding issues that prevented the library from working on Mono * Fixed incorrect remote property in IS_NCN * Fixed bug PLT_REMOTE in PlayerTypes was incorrect * Fixed TyreCompound enum and added TYRE_NONE * Fixed issue with IS_AXM Info list being set to wrong size
